<https://medjat.irokosociety.org/id/library/GG2WDSFL>
  a schema:ScholarlyArticle ;
  schema:name "The legacies of slavery in and out of Africa" ;
  schema:url <https://medjat.irokosociety.org/library/?item=GG2WDSFL> ;
  dcterms:isPartOf <https://medjat.irokosociety.org/id/collection/medjat-library> ;
  dcterms:identifier "zotero:6479329:GG2WDSFL" ;
  schema:description "Abstract The slave trades out of Africa represent one of the most significant forced migration experiences in history. In this paper, I illustrate their long-term consequences on contemporaneous socio-economic outcomes, drawing from my own previous work on the topic and from an extensive review of the available literature. I first consider the influence of the slave trade on the “sending” countries in Africa, with attention to their economic, institutional, demographic, and social implications. Next, I evaluate the consequences of the slave trade on the “receiving” countries in the Americas. Here, I distinguish between the case of Latin America and that of the USA. Overall, I show that the slave trades exert a lasting impact along several contemporaneous socio-economic dimensions and across diverse areas of the world. JEL Classification: J47, J15, O15, N30, P48, Z10" ;
  schema:author "Graziella Bertocchi" ;
  schema:datePublished "2016" ;
  schema:publisher "IZA Journal of Migration" ;
  schema:sameAs <https://doi.org/10.1186/s40176-016-0072-0> ;
  dcterms:identifier "doi:10.1186/s40176-016-0072-0" ;
  dcterms:subject "Colonialism, slavery, and trade", "Culture, Economy, and Development Studies", "Migration and Labor Dynamics" .
